      h1 Looking for a new hobby?
      p Sunderland Rowing Club runs learn-to-row courses during the year. These courses typically consist of approximately two hours where our volunteer coaches will take you through the basics of rowing technique, both on a Concept2 RowErg and on the water. 
      p Rowing is all about using smooth, controlled movements to push and pull. Whether you're on land or in a boat, the basic steps are the same. In these sessions we will teach you the correct body movements and positions that move a boat effectively. Our dedicated team of coaches are here to provide you with as much or as little detail as you require, so feel free to ask questions along the way.
      p Please remember that weather conditions may vary and suitable clothing is always required. British Rowing does provide a more detailed itinerary in this <a href="https://www.britishrowing.org/knowledge/rower-development/british-rowing-technique/what-to-wear">What to Wear for Rowing</a> article, but please know that no specialist clothing is required.
      p When you complete the course, you will then be able to continue at our club as a member and further your rowing ability. Once you are at a reasonably competent standard, there are then opportunities to race competitively, or you can continue to row at the club and enjoy our social atmosphere. 

